@page "/webforms-parity"

<PageTitle>WebForms to Blazor Parity</PageTitle>

<h1>WebForms → Blazor component parity guide</h1>

<p>This page tracks and validates the Phase 3 port of common System.Web.UI control patterns into Blazor.</p>

<table class="table table-striped">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Legacy WebForms control</th>
            <th>Blazor equivalent</th>
            <th>Status</th>
            <th>Notes</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>Label</td>
            <td>&lt;Text&gt; or &lt;span&gt;</td>
            <td>Done</td>
            <td>Simple inline text binding with @@bind if editable.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>TextBox</td>
            <td>&lt;InputText&gt;</td>
            <td>In progress</td>
            <td>Support validation with EditForm + DataAnnotations.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Button</td>
            <td>&lt;Button&gt; / &lt;MudBlazorButton&gt;</td>
            <td>Done</td>
            <td>Event callback is @@onclick.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>GridView</td>
            <td>Table + @@foreach or third-party grid</td>
            <td>Pending</td>
            <td>Requires pagination + sort logic ported from old code.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>DropDownList</td>
            <td>&lt;InputSelect&gt;</td>
            <td>In progress</td>
            <td>Map Items collection to IEnumerable.</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Next migration work items</h2>
<ol>
    <li>Implement a form-based login flow that mirrors `AdministrationLogonForm` behavior. <a href="/administration-logon">Try the pilot login page</a>.</li>
    <li>Create a `VwgFormBase` component to encapsulate common styling and header/footer from existing app templates.</li>
    <li>Write Playwright tests for login → dashboard flow and basic DataGrid scenario.</li>
</ol>